# axl/spec.axlr
# AXL-R — Agent eXecution Language Rules v0.4

@META
id: axl-r-spec
v: 0.5
kind: axlr
modified: @20260709
purpose: compact normative rules for coding/infra agents

@COMMON_MISTAKES
m1: Do not treat S as optional when unblocked; S means should unless stronger rule blocks.
m2: Do not report done when any acceptance criterion is unsatisfied or unverified.
m3: Do not use stale memory as governing policy; reread current policy chain.
m4: Do not expand read set unboundedly; compute ReadSet(T).
m5: Do not retry failed shell commands before classifying the error.
m6: Do not silently resolve rule conflicts; apply priority, specificity, else stop_report(conflict).
m7: Do not turn AXL-R rules into mutable task logs; use AXL-S for state.
m8: Do not store secrets inline; use *ENV_VAR references.
m9: Do not apply or publish a rule set with duplicate rule identifiers.

@RULE_SHAPE
canonical: R[id]: scope | trigger -> norm action [pre] [read] [verify] [except] [effect] [emit]
schema: {id,scope,trigger,norm,action,pre?,read?,verify?,except?,effect?,emit?}

@PRIORITY
order: safety ≻ platform_policy ≻ user_instruction ≻ repo_policy ≻ local_policy ≻ task_AC ≻ preference
conflict: conflict(a,b)->choose(max_priority); tie->choose(more_specific); unresolved->stop_report(conflict)

@DOMAIN_OBJECTS
T: task
AC: acceptance_criterion
Repo: repository_root
p: path
Δ: changed_paths
S: symbol
Cmd: shell_command
Tool: external_tool|MCP|API|connector
Ctx: context_payload
Ev: evidence
Plan: ordered_task_plan
Step: plan_step
Patch: file_modification
Gate: verification_gate
Claim: assertion
Risk: possible_failure_mode
State: durable_state
Mem: memory_item
CtxRec: context_record

@RULES authoring
RAXL001: author(rule_set) -> M verify(unique(rule_id,transitive_import_scope)) ≺ publish(rule_set)
RAXL002: add(incoming_rules,existing_rules) -> M detect(identifier_conflicts(incoming_rules,existing_rules))
RAXL003: identifier_conflict(incoming_rule,existing_rule) -> M preserve(id(existing_rule)) ∧ M renumber(incoming_rule)
RAXL004: duplicate(rule_id) -> M stop_report(identifier_conflict) ∧ F apply_or_publish(ambiguous_rule_set)
RAXL005: renumber(incoming_rule) -> M allocate(valid_free_id) ∧ M update(all_references(incoming_rule))
RAXL006: allocate(valid_free_id) -> M choose(first_free_id_in_intended_section)
RAXL007: child_rule(incoming_rule,parent) ∧ free_suffix(parent) -> Pref(allocate(next_free_suffix(parent)),allocate(new_numeric_parent))
RAXL008: no_free_suffix(parent) -> M allocate(next_free_numeric_parent) ∧ F invent(noncanonical_suffix)
RAXL009: renumber(existing_rule) -> F unless(explicit_migration ∧ complete_reference_update ∧ validation)
RAXL010: renumber(rule) -> M verify(unique(rule_id,transitive_import_scope) ∧ references_resolve ∧ ordering_valid)
RAXL011: unresolved(identifier_conflict) -> M stop_report(conflicting_ids ∧ affected_rules) ∧ F guess_or_overwrite
